# 🔧 Git & Commit Rules

## Auto-commit expectation
- After each AI-generated change, immediately stage and commit.
- Keep working tree clean; avoid uncommitted state between AI steps.

## Commit message style
- Language: English, concise, feature-focused.
- Format: `<type>: <short summary>` (lowercase type).
- Recommended types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `style`, `test`.
- Keep subject ≤ 72 chars; state the main change or added capability.
- Examples:
  - `feat: add auto-summary for daily sessions`
  - `fix: handle missing youtube link defaults`
  - `chore: update cursor rule files`

## What to avoid
- ❌ No ticket IDs unless provided.
- ❌ No verbose or multi-sentence subjects.
- ❌ No non-English text.

## When to skip auto-commit
- Skip only if user explicitly says “don’t commit” for a change.
- Otherwise, commit every AI-applied change batch.
